Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:06.23,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.23,0:00:11.86,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.57,0:00:17.66,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:22.37,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.00,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:29.34,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.89,0:02:04.31,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}To you, children of God, who live on this earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:07.98,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}pray and believe, and you shall be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:11.98,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The Sun God Leto shines light upon you to show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:11.98,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys street performers or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:16.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where in the world did you get that idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:17.86,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:19.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.24,0:02:24.12,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:26.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that, we'll fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:27.96,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Fix", you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.96,0:02:29.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.46,0:02:33.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:39.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:41.68,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's quite a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:44.18,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're able to perform miracles, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:47.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:50.31,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time I've seen anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:52.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've never heard of us, the Elric Brothers, before?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:54.36,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,"Elric"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:56.11,Default,Man2,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:58.90,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,The Fullmetal Alchemist, Edward Elric!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:02.57,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you're that rumored genius alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:06.41,Default,Man3,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I get it! Your other name is "Fullmetal" because of this suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.41,0:03:09.45,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No... You have the wrong person...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.92,0:03:14.04,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That little guy over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.04,0:03:16.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a pea-sized runt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.17,0:03:21.88,Default-alt,Corn,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Pray and believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.59,0:03:22.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, what the heck is this broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:25.72,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the High Priest Cornello...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:31.64,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,He came here a few years ago and preached to us about the path of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.64,0:03:35.90,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,"God will grant eternity to the living and resurrection to the dead."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.90,0:03:38.23,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,And proof of it all are the miracles that he produces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:42.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Resurrection to the dead", eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:43.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds fishy to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.21,0:03:59.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they were talking about, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:00.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:03.84,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty obvious from that transmutation response that it's alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.84,0:04:06.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But he's totally ignoring the concept of equivalent exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.72,0:04:11.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a rule that you can only produce something from matter of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.35,0:04:13.89,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He changed a flower to a mineral, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.31,0:04:16.10,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:18.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.27,0:04:20.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:34.04,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,God... please listen to my wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:35.75,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Please bring back-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.75,0:04:38.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so this is Mr. Leto.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.29,0:04:41.30,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Are you interested in the religion of Leto?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:44.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah. Unfortunately, I'm an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.47,0:04:47.05,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:51.85,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Believing and honoring God,\Nand living in gratitude and hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:54.18,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,How glorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.27,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,If you believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.11,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll grow taller!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:00.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:02.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't mean it in a bad way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.69,0:05:06.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Resurrection to the dead"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.86,0:05:08.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you seriously believe something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.87,0:05:09.49,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:15.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Water, 35L.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:16.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Carbon, 20kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:18.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ammonia, 4L.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.13,0:05:20.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lime, 1.5kg.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:21.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Phosphorus, 800g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:23.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Salt, 250g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:24.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Niter, 100g.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:26.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.47,0:05:27.55,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,...What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:33.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the ingredients that make up an average adult human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:40.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx96}We know this from our advances in science, but there\Nhaven't been any reports of successful human transmutations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.27,0:05:44.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You really think that praying would solve something that even science couldn't solve?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.69,0:05:49.07,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,"Pray and believe, and your wishes shall be."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:50.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:55.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,you can buy these basic ingredients at the market with a kid's pocket money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are made pretty cheaply, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:03.55,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,People are not things. Those words are blasphemy to our creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:04.96,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,You'll suffer divine punishment for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:09.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are scientists, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:12.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We don't believe in creators or the existence of a God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.56,0:06:17.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the solution to the creation principle of this world and pursuing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.31,0:06:25.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty ironic we're the closest things to God\Nin a sense, even though we have no need for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:28.57,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you're on the same level as God?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:30.11,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,How arrogant!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Arrogant, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.45,0:06:34.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this from a mythical tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:42.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"The hero who gets too close to the sun shall have\Nhis wax wings plucked and be dropped to the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:43.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.50,0:06:51.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lady, will Mr. Leto save a scientist like me?\NEven though I was thinking something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:56.14,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. He will accept reformers at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.27,0:07:00.64,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,High Priest, there are people who wish to have a meeting with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:03.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Two of them. A child and a man in a suit of armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:05.65,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They call themselves the "Elric Brothers".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.65,0:07:08.32,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy. Dismiss them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:11.49,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, wait... Did you say... the Elric Brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:14.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's what they said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.32,0:07:19.37,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is going to be trouble.\NIt's the Fullmetal Alchemist, Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.37,0:07:21.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The... man in the armor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.16,0:07:22.92,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:25.88,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What is a State Alchemist doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:28.42,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that our plan has been...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:32.43,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Those dogs of the military must have a good sense of smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.84,0:07:34.97,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.51,0:07:39.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The High Priest is a very busy man, and he usually cannot find time for such matters, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:41.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You folks are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.43,0:07:45.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the trouble. I'll try to make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.61,0:07:48.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's get this over with as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.57,0:07:53.70,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Priest, what are you doing?!{I'll find a good term for this later ~koki}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:59.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, these people are heathens who are trying to ensnare the High Priest. They are evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:00.29,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:03.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So... let's get this over with quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:14.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:15.80,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,So noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:22.52,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the holy order, Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:24.02,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Cornello!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:27.15,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like some of us were rather hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:29.07,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for their rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.07,0:08:32.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It really doesn't feel like an apology when you're looking down at us from a high place like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:34.70,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here for our dogma?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:40.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have a lot of things I want to learn from you... say,\Na method for tricking your followers with petty alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:43.58,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:47.17,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have you putting my miracles and alchemy on the same level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:51.67,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How's this? Can this be achieved through alchemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:54.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's precisely what I'm concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:58.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,For some strange reason, you can perform\Ntransmutations while clearly ignoring the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:09:01.43,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why it isn't alchemy-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:03.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So I was thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.89,0:09:12.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If you had the legendary amplifier that allows alchemists to perform the impossible, it would be possible in your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.61,0:09:13.44,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:18.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Frankly, the Philosopher's Stone. Isn't that what your ring is made of?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:22.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That was a long search.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:24.45,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is just an ordinary ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.45,0:09:27.79,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,God has allowed me to perform miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.79,0:09:29.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Still gonna play dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:33.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll have to get my hands on you and ask your body for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.21,0:09:37.47,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be an incorrigible heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:38.05,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.59,0:09:39.55,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:42.56,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Pick up that pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.97,0:09:44.81,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:50.31,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Now shoot the Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:54.19,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,I... can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:56.99,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My words are God's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:09:59.24,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This is God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:02.20,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:06.96,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.96,0:10:09.71,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Who was the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:14.80,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,...who rescued you from your despair\Nafter you lost your love in an accident last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:18.05,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, Sir Cornello...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:21.76,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It was I who rescued you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:23.81,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,And what did I promise you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.06,0:10:26.31,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd revive him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:31.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... I'm not the one you're supposed to be aiming at...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:37.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the Fullmetal Alchemist, got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.36,0:10:39.24,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, {\i1}you're{\i0} the one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.03,0:10:45.37,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry... I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:47.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's a swindler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:47.95,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No, he isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:51.50,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to revive him with his miracles!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:53.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:00.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.80,0:11:07.60,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Good work. God is rejoicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.60,0:11:10.06,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Now, shoot the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:13.06,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you make your followers do terrible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:13.98,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.36,0:11:16.48,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:18.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:19.99,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...this is how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:24.03,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,An empty suit of armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:28.41,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,This, itself, is evidence of their evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:30.83,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.67,0:11:39.26,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your first time seeing a chimera?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:43.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you made something like this with your Philosopher's Stone, too, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:48.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I should probably arm myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.73,0:11:57.73,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Without a transmutation circle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:01.49,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I guess your title of "State Alchemist" has to come with {\i1}something{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:02.20,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:10.37,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like those claws that cut through iron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:13.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:19.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, my leg is a bit special.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:21.34,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Bite him to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:27.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, stupid cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:28.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get a good taste of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:35.98,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,That arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.44,0:12:37.98,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,...and a brother without his body...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:40.73,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:44.57,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Fullmetal Alchemist... you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:47.07,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You've done it, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:49.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get down here, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:52.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the difference in our skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:00.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get down here, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:02.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the difference in our skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.92,0:13:07.93,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, these guys have committed the greatest taboo alchemists can commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:10.76,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:14.06,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They tried to revive the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:21.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"The hero who gets too close to the sun shall have\Nhis wax wings plucked and be dropped to the earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:23.61,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:28.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is the body of a sinner who encroached upon God's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.57,0:13:31.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Rose, are you really prepared to be like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:35.00,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:39.13,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself a State Alchemist? You make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:40.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:43.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do anything without\Nthe Philosopher's Stone, third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.38,0:13:47.63,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,High Priest, please give us the stone before you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:52.18,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How ridiculous! Fools who stepped into God's territory!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:56.39,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you to his side, once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.81,0:14:07.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, God seems to hate me,\Nso he'll probably send me back even if I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:14.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.96,0:14:23.59,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?! After them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:26.84,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They are heathens who bring evil to the order! Catch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:31.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:34.14,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you can do unarmed, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:37.02,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Just give up before you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:46.07,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down just because he's a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:54.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Get it now, Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:14:59.16,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Cornello shot at us, even though you were with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:01.17,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But that's because you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.54,0:15:06.67,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Is that story true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.21,0:15:12.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We just wanted to see Mom's smiling face again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.30,0:15:16.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But the transmutation failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.68,0:15:19.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't even look human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.56,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We learned our mistake the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:28.28,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,People cannot be revived... even our mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:30.90,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true... because...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.90,0:15:33.62,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The fundamental basis of alchemy is the concept of equivalent exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:36.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The price we paid for the human transmutation was huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.45,0:15:41.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother lost his left leg, and I lost my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:44.88,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:48.05,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother drew it with his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:53.30,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been painful for him,\Nafter having his left leg taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.89,0:16:01.39,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But Brother affixed my soul to this suit and gave up his right arm as compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:06.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I want to fix my brother's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:09.82,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother wants to get my body back, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:14.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But we may die trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:19.83,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's the path we've chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:22.71,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But, Sir Cornello could...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:24.00,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:27.96,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you two can't, he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:31.01,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He could do it! He will!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:36.05,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You brat! You'd better be prepared!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.05,0:16:38.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, let's have a heart-to-heart talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:41.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to know the secret behind that stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:45.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I call for the army to mobilize?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:47.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,To inspect the stone, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:51.82,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:54.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do with the Philosopher's Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.11,0:16:57.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need that pitiful order if you have the stone, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:05.29,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,The order will produce followers that will joyfully give up their lives for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:08.38,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,They would be an undefeatable army that does not fear even death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.38,0:17:09.79,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:14.80,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be stripping this country away in a few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:18.01,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,By using the Philosopher's Stone and my stupid followers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:21.60,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I could share some of the leftovers with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:26.35,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.85,0:17:29.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This{\i0} is why I called you third-rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:37.32,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Y...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:38.57,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.82,0:17:42.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There are no such things as miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:44.91,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They were all thanks to the power of the Philosopher's Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:47.75,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:49.33,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,When did you flip on that switch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.33,0:17:50.33,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,When?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:51.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,From the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:53.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's all been leaked, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:55.34,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:17:57.55,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You brat!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.34,0:17:59.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:04.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Told ya. We're on totally different levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:08.56,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.99,0:18:19.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rebound!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.61,0:18:22.28,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not giving up yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:25.79,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:29.46,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,God's hand!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:54.77,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My words are God's words. This fist is God's fist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:57.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"God's fist", you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:01.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If you like it so much, I'll let you have a taste of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:21.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.68,0:19:23.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now give me the Philosopher's Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:31.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It... broke? What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:36.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How could the Philosopher's Stone break? It's supposed to be a perfect substance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:37.57,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:39.15,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't hear about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:40.40,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,P-P-P-Please don't hurt me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:42.61,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Please! I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.61,0:19:44.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So it was a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.28,0:19:48.16,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything without the stone! Please, have mercy!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.16,0:19:52.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I finally thought we'd be able to get our bodies back, and it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.50,0:19:54.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.46,0:19:57.80,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,U-Umm, what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.96,0:20:01.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Go wherever you want!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:02.80,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.85,0:20:07.14,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What about the Philosopher's Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:09.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.14,0:20:10.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.52,0:20:16.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought we'd finally be able to get your body back...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.19,0:20:17.82,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the Philosopher's Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:20.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Rose...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:25.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I just say that it was a fake?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:27.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And in any case, it broke on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.07,0:20:27.91,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:29.54,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,You're planning to keep it for yourselves, aren't you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.45,0:20:33.08,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,To fix your bodies... right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:35.00,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,And you want to meet your mother again, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:36.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:39.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The dead cannot be revived...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:41.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Never...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:44.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.01,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,But he said that he'd be able to bring him back...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.76,0:20:51.52,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,He said that if I prayed, it would come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:53.81,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,That a miracle would occur...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.56,0:20:59.65,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to cling to from now on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:01.61,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:04.40,Default,Rose,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.61,0:21:09.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Decide that for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:14.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get up and take a step. Walk forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:17.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've got two fine legs on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.25,0:21:21.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to cling to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:29.89,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:31.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Let us see the High Priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.76,0:21:33.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Were you guys tricking us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:35.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Open this door!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.19,0:21:40.27,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,My plans... ruined by a brat like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.27,0:21:42.82,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously. What a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.82,0:21:45.90,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,All you had to do was to wreak a bit of havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:47.32,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.32,0:21:48.70,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Lust?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.70,0:21:50.83,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Can I eat this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.83,0:21:52.91,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,No, Gluttony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:55.33,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,If you eat something like that, you'll get a stomachache.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.33,0:21:58.37,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,How dare... How dare you all make fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.96,0:22:06.30,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,You're not needed anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.35,0:22:13.60,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,It was just starting to liven up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.22,0:22:16.18,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we have to start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.81,0:22:18.69,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Father will get mad at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.31,0:22:23.23,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I wonder what we should do next...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.91,0:24:06.92,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al visit East City, home of Eastern Headquarters, to report the incident in Lior.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:12.84,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,And they meet Shou Tucker,\Nthe Sewing-Life Alchemist, and his daughter, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.01,0:24:18.35,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.35,0:24:21.35,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 4, An Alchemist's Anguish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.43,0:24:26.40,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,An encounter. Is that the beginning of suffering?
